Sentencas: In this contribution, we report investigation of metal supported cells with a La0.1Sr0.9TiO3- (LST) based fuel electrode.
Titulo: Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode

Sentencas: The cells are prepared on a substrate made of a porous NiCrAl metal foam infiltrated with NiO and LST materials.
Titulo: Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode

Sentencas: The functional anode layer, consisting of LST mixed with a Gd0.1Ce0.9O2- (GDC), is produced by screen printing.
Titulo: Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode

Sentencas: Nickel metal is infiltrated in the backbone to enhance electronic and catalytic properties.
Titulo: Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode

Sentencas: The electrolyte made of an 1 m + 0.5 mu m thick Zr0.84Y0.16O2- (YSZ) layer followed by a 2 m thick GDC layer, is fabricated by wet ceramic processing and electron beam physical vapor deposition (EB-PVD), respectively.
Titulo: Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode

Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3- (LSCF) is employed as a cathode material.
Titulo: Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode
Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C and at a cell voltage of 0.7 V, the typically achieved power density value is up to 0.40 W cm(-2).
Titulo: Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode

Sentencas: With less than 2% variation for 50 cycles, the OCV showed an excellent stability as a function of redox cycles, demonstrating that an electrolyte as thin as 3 mu m maintains its integrity, despite the harsh operating conditions.
Titulo: Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode

Sentencas: This highlights the potential of perovskite based fuel electrodes in metal supported cells, and paves the way to the next generation of cells' design.
Titulo: Performances and Limitations of Metal Supported Cells with Strontium Titanate based Fuel Electrode
